objectives.name: Primary Efficacy Objective - Body Weight Reduction
objectives.text: To demonstrate that tirzepatide 5 mg, 10 mg, and 15 mg once weekly is superior to placebo for body weight reduction at 72 weeks

objectives.name: Key Secondary Objective - Body Weight at 20 Weeks Pooled Dose
objectives.text: To demonstrate that pooled tirzepatide 10 mg and 15 mg once weekly is superior to placebo for body weight reduction at 20 weeks

objectives.name: Key Secondary Objective - Body Weight at 72 Weeks By Dose
objectives.text: To demonstrate that tirzepatide 10 mg and 15 mg once weekly separately is superior to placebo for body weight reduction including ≥20% body weight reduction from randomization at 72 weeks

objectives.name: Key Secondary Objective - SF-36v2 Physical Functioning at 72 Weeks Pooled Dose
objectives.text: To demonstrate that pooled tirzepatide 10 mg and 15 mg once weekly is superior to placebo for SF-36v2 acute form Physical Functioning domain score at 72 weeks

objectives.name: Key Secondary Objective - Lipid Parameters at 72 Weeks Pooled Dose
objectives.text: To demonstrate that tirzepatide (all doses combined) is superior to placebo for lipid parameters including non-HDL cholesterol and HDL cholesterol at 72 weeks

objectives.name: Additional Secondary Objective - Lipid Parameters at 72 Weeks Pooled Dose
objectives.text: To evaluate the effect of tirzepatide (all doses combined) compared to placebo on lipid parameters including LDL cholesterol and total cholesterol at 72 weeks

objectives.name: Safety Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate the safety and tolerability of tirzepatide once weekly compared to placebo in participants without type 2 diabetes who have obesity or are overweight with weight-related comorbidities

objectives.name: Objective - Progression to Type 2 Diabetes in Prediabetes Participants
objectives.text: To evaluate the effect of tirzepatide on progression to type 2 diabetes in participants with prediabetes at randomization during the additional 2-year treatment period

endpoints.name: Primary Endpoint - Percent Change in Body Weight
endpoints.text: Percent change from baseline in body weight at 72 weeks

endpoints.name: Primary Endpoint - Body Weight Reduction ≥5%
endpoints.text: Proportion of participants achieving ≥5% body weight reduction from randomization at 72 weeks

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint - Percent Change in Body Weight at 20 Weeks
endpoints.text: Percent change from baseline in body weight at 20 weeks for pooled tirzepatide 10 mg and 15 mg doses

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint - Body Weight Reduction ≥20% at 72 Weeks
endpoints.text: Proportion of participants achieving ≥20% body weight reduction from randomization at 72 weeks

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint - SF-36v2 Physical Functioning Domain Score
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in SF-36v2 acute form Physical Functioning domain score at 72 weeks

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint - Non-HDL Cholesterol
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in non-HDL cholesterol at 72 weeks

endpoints.name: Key Secondary Endpoint - HDL Cholesterol
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in HDL cholesterol at 72 weeks

endpoints.name: Additional Secondary Endpoint - LDL Cholesterol
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in LDL cholesterol at 72 weeks

endpoints.name: Additional Secondary Endpoint - Total Cholesterol
endpoints.text: Change from baseline in total cholesterol at 72 weeks

endpoints.name: Safety Endpoint - Adverse Events
endpoints.text: Incidence and severity of treatment-emergent adverse events

endpoints.name: Safety Endpoint - Tolerability
endpoints.text: Tolerability of tirzepatide as assessed by discontinuation rates due to adverse events

endpoints.name: Endpoint - Incident Diabetes
endpoints.text: Incidence of type 2 diabetes in participants with prediabetes at randomization during the additional 2-year treatment period

estimands.name: Primary Estimand - Treatment Policy Strategy
estimands.text: Treatment effect on body weight reduction at 72 weeks in the ITT population using treatment policy strategy for intercurrent events
